==English==

{{rank|sitting|Christ|begin|789|wait|laughed|opportunity|lines}}

===Etymology===
From Old Northern French [[waitier]], a variant of Old French [[guatier]] (modern [[guetter]] ‘watch for’), from Germanic.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/weɪt/}}
*{{audio|en-us-wait.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪt|-eɪt]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}
# ''(transitive)'' to delay movement or action until the arrival or occurence of; to [[await]]
#:''You'll just have to '''wait''' your turn.''
# ''(intransitive)'' To [[delay]] [[movement]] or [[action]] until some event or time; to [[remain]] neglected or in readiness
#: '''''Wait''' here until your car arrives.''
# ''(intransitive)'' To serve customers in a [[restaurant]] or other [[eating]] [[establishment]].
#: ''She used to '''wait''' down at the Dew Drop Inn.''

